sect1.para:
Another distinguishing aspect of &Distribution;, that also "complies"
with the KISS principe is the &Distribution; package manager. &Distribution; 
does not have complex package manager like RPM. Packages are normal tgz
(tar/gzip) files, mostly with an additional installation script and
a package description. Tgz is much more powerful than RPM for novice
users and avoids dependency problems. Another famous feature of &Distribution; 
are the BSD-like initialization scripts of &Distribution;. &Distribution; 
has one initialization script for each runlevel insteas of a script
for eacht daemon. It allow you to tweak with your system easily,
without the need to write net init scripts yourself.
